<div id="outline-container-org630dc4c" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org630dc4c">Data type</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org630dc4c">
<p>
A data type defines a certain domain of values and it defines what operations can be done ith it.
Example in nim you can add and subtract ints, basicly primitive types
</p>

<p>
User types are types that you me or user of a language would define.
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orge41ed67" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orge41ed67">Abstract Data Types (ADT)</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orge41ed67">
<p>
These are like user defined types which define what operations can be preformed on them.
The functions body are defined and ho it is done!
</p>

<p>
In short they are a black box
</p>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org1cf513d" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org1cf513d">A stack ADT</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-org1cf513d">
<p>
A Stack consists of elements of the same type in a sequential order
Some example functions
</p>

<ul class="org-ul">
<li>push insert a element</li>
<li>pop delete a element</li>
<li>isEmpty checks if its empty</li>
<li>isFull checks if its full</li>
<li>initialize creating it with no elements</li>
</ul>
